definitions.definition: Ambiguous ; liable to more than one interpretation .
examples: The remark she made comparing her life with that of a fish was unclear .

definitions.definition: Not easy to see or read ; indecipherable or unreadable .
examples: From such a long distance away, the name on the signpost was unclear .

definitions.definition: Not having a clear idea; uncertain.
examples: I'm still unclear about what she meant by that remark.

main_definition: Ambiguous ; liable to more than one interpretation .
secondary_definitions: Not easy to see or read ; indecipherable or unreadable .
Not having a clear idea; uncertain.
